01:37.934 --> 01:40.801
[telephones ringing,
indistinct conversations]

01:42.471 --> 01:44.671
What the fuck?

01:44.673 --> 01:46.806
- Mafee wants to see you.
- [Bobby] I just waved him in.

01:46.808 --> 01:48.374
He wanted me to ask you permission.

01:48.376 --> 01:49.976
Permission for what?

01:49.978 --> 01:52.012
He comes in here all the fucking time.

01:52.014 --> 01:54.614
Door's always open. You know that.
I love Mafee.

01:54.616 --> 01:56.215
He wants to talk about BioLance.

01:56.217 --> 01:57.651
Oh. Well, in that case, fire him.

01:57.653 --> 02:00.119
Yeah. He said that you said he's
not allowed to bring it up.

02:00.121 --> 02:02.622
No, he can, if he wants to get fired.

02:02.624 --> 02:04.223
Right, but if he doesn't bring it up,

02:04.225 --> 02:05.924
he thinks you're gonna lose 400 million.

02:05.926 --> 02:07.560
And since he's executing the trade...

02:07.562 --> 02:10.029
He thinks I'll fire him then.

02:10.031 --> 02:12.731
Sticky. I can see how that's sticky.

02:12.733 --> 02:14.467
Can he come in?

02:14.469 --> 02:16.635
Of course. I love Mafee.

02:20.074 --> 02:21.506
[handle clicks,
indistinct conversations]

02:21.508 --> 02:22.708
It's okay?

02:22.710 --> 02:24.376
We'll see.

02:25.780 --> 02:28.413
Axe, special announcement call

02:28.415 --> 02:31.950
from BioLance is in nine minutes.

02:31.952 --> 02:34.686
I've been losing sleep over
it, and I sleep like a bear.

02:34.688 --> 02:36.321
Brown or polar?

02:36.323 --> 02:37.522
Which hibernate?

02:37.524 --> 02:39.191
They all... hibernate.

02:39.193 --> 02:41.092
They're bears.

02:41.094 --> 02:43.861
Then both, but not lately.

02:43.863 --> 02:45.263
[Bobby] Uh-huh.

02:45.265 --> 02:47.599
I can pare our position before the call.

02:47.601 --> 02:49.834
We can still make 10%.

02:49.836 --> 02:52.036
If we hold and I'm right,
what do we make then?

02:52.038 --> 02:53.537
We double our money.

02:53.539 --> 02:55.673
If we were a benchmark
fund, ten would be great.

02:55.675 --> 02:57.241
But we are no benchmark fund.

02:57.243 --> 02:59.410
I'm just afraid we're gonna lose.

02:59.412 --> 03:02.513
All my research is telling me
that approval is a coin flip.

03:02.515 --> 03:04.381
Right. Do Ben Kim and
all the other analysts

03:04.383 --> 03:06.250
agree with you?

03:06.252 --> 03:07.518
To a man.

03:11.557 --> 03:13.324
First, I told you yesterday
and the day before

03:13.326 --> 03:14.891
that I understood the risks.

03:14.893 --> 03:17.261
I've done the channel checks.
I've done the homework.

03:17.263 --> 03:19.396
BioLance's inhibitor is
gonna be lights out.

03:19.398 --> 03:22.465
Six other companies have
inhibitors in the works.

03:22.467 --> 03:25.568
Only one's gonna win
approval and market share.

03:25.570 --> 03:28.371
That's why I think we
should wait, get in later.

03:28.373 --> 03:30.440
Oh. Second, you're fired.

03:30.442 --> 03:32.943
I'm fired?

03:32.945 --> 03:34.611
That's what he said.

03:34.613 --> 03:38.314
We're already in BioLance.
That's where the win is.

03:38.316 --> 03:41.384
I-I just don't see what
the difference maker is.

03:41.386 --> 03:43.586
<i>I'm</i> the difference maker.

03:45.923 --> 03:47.290
I tried.

03:47.292 --> 03:49.058
You tried.

03:51.028 --> 03:52.228
And now I'm fired.

03:52.230 --> 03:54.897
Goodbye, Mafee.

03:58.269 --> 03:59.601
<i>[woman on speakerphone]
The next voice you hear</i>

03:59.603 --> 04:02.604
<i>will be the BioLance
CEO, Brooks Wellever.</i>

04:02.606 --> 04:04.306
- [telephone beeps]
<i>-[Brooks] So you all know</i>

04:04.308 --> 04:07.042
<i>how important the development
of our SGLT 2 inhibitor</i>

04:07.044 --> 04:10.179
<i>for treatment of Type 2
diabetes is to this company,</i>

04:10.181 --> 04:12.713
<i>how deep our investment has been.</i>

04:12.715 --> 04:14.649
<i>And I wish I had better news.</i>

04:14.651 --> 04:16.985
<i>We were just notified by the FDA</i>

04:16.987 --> 04:18.286
<i>that we were denied approval.</i>

04:18.288 --> 04:20.288
[employees sigh, groan]

04:20.290 --> 04:22.824
<i>[Brooks] We estimate a time
horizon of five more years</i>

04:22.826 --> 04:24.025
<i>to complete fixes.</i>

04:24.027 --> 04:25.827
<i>But at our current burn rate of cash,</i>

04:25.829 --> 04:27.528
<i>we only have three years
of operating ex...</i>

04:27.530 --> 04:30.531
[telephone beeps]

04:30.533 --> 04:33.567
<i>♪ tense, pulsating music ♪</i>

04:42.211 --> 04:45.245
<i>[music volume increases]</i>

04:51.120 --> 04:54.154
<i>♪♪♪</i>

04:57.126 --> 04:59.293
[employees murmuring]

04:59.295 --> 05:00.560
What's the damage?

05:00.562 --> 05:02.228
Stock is halted until the morning,

05:02.230 --> 05:03.763
but there are no bids in sight.

05:03.765 --> 05:06.733
- It's gonna be ugly.
- [Wags] Shit.

05:06.735 --> 05:09.769
430 million dollar loss.

05:09.771 --> 05:11.070
Could turn into twice that.

05:11.072 --> 05:14.106
<i>♪♪♪</i>

05:16.277 --> 05:18.878
[telephone ringing in distance]

05:18.880 --> 05:21.914
[indistinct conversations]

05:28.223 --> 05:29.989
[door closes]

05:29.991 --> 05:33.025
[footsteps thudding]

05:35.596 --> 05:37.996
[object rattles and thuds]
- What are you doing?

05:37.998 --> 05:40.632
- [chair clatters]
- You fired me.

05:40.634 --> 05:42.501
You know never to listen
to me about shit like that

05:42.503 --> 05:44.370
between 9:30 and 4:00.

05:44.372 --> 05:46.171
How could I fire you?

05:46.173 --> 05:48.340
- I love you, Mafee.
- [pats shoulder]

05:48.342 --> 05:51.042
[indistinct conversations continue]

05:51.044 --> 05:54.379
[footsteps thudding]

05:54.381 --> 05:58.449
<i>♪ pensive music playing ♪</i>

05:58.451 --> 05:59.817
[objects rustle]

06:02.722 --> 06:05.757
[indistinct conversations]

06:07.994 --> 06:09.794
- [Wendy] Hey.
- [Maria] Wendy.

06:09.796 --> 06:13.498
[exhales] Oh, I am so glad
you're thinking about us.

06:13.500 --> 06:16.066
Hey, Roma wants to give
you the tour herself.

06:17.537 --> 06:19.036
How are you?

06:19.038 --> 06:21.138
Work is a happy place now.

06:21.140 --> 06:24.474
[Maria] Come on. I'll introduce you.

06:24.476 --> 06:25.709
[Wendy] Great space.

06:25.711 --> 06:28.312
I have an eye for it. Even
better one for talent.

06:28.314 --> 06:30.414
I knew that as soon
as you snagged Maria.

06:30.416 --> 06:32.449
She's a perfect fit.

06:32.451 --> 06:35.886
We value fit, culture, more than most.

06:35.888 --> 06:39.056
That's why 60% or so
of our PMs are women.

06:39.058 --> 06:42.626
Makes it easier to practice
socially responsible investing.

06:42.628 --> 06:43.860
Is that the mission?

06:43.862 --> 06:45.595
The mission is profit.

06:45.597 --> 06:48.031
But me and a few of the senior partners,

06:48.033 --> 06:49.265
we came up at a time

06:49.267 --> 06:51.635
when Wall Street was all cock and balls

06:51.637 --> 06:53.603
- ...and no brains.
- [chuckles]

06:53.605 --> 06:56.372
We try to practice with a
little less ego around here

06:56.374 --> 07:00.910
in a more collaborative,
inclusive environment.

07:00.912 --> 07:03.146
But it's a delicate balance.

07:03.148 --> 07:04.580
You don't want a bunch
of guys running around

07:04.582 --> 07:05.949
with sawed-off shotguns,

07:05.951 --> 07:07.283
but you don't want scented candles

07:07.285 --> 07:09.052
and an aversion to risk either.

07:09.054 --> 07:11.421
- That's for fucking sure.
- [chuckles]

07:11.423 --> 07:14.022
We need someone to curate that balance,

07:14.024 --> 07:15.458
someone who's been through the wars,

07:15.460 --> 07:17.526
who's seen the other side.

07:17.528 --> 07:19.628
You want me to make
your people assassins.

07:19.630 --> 07:21.129
We want them to be able

07:21.131 --> 07:23.532
to access that mentality when needed,

07:23.534 --> 07:25.000
with great accuracy.

07:25.002 --> 07:27.636
Yeah. Assassins. It's
kind of my specialty.

07:27.638 --> 07:28.938
I know.

07:28.940 --> 07:30.638
No other performance
coach in the industry

07:30.640 --> 07:32.207
would be a better fit.

07:32.209 --> 07:34.476
And you're already an investor.

07:34.478 --> 07:35.844
[indistinct conversations]

07:35.846 --> 07:37.379
We need you,

07:37.381 --> 07:39.781
and you wanna be here.

07:39.783 --> 07:41.716
[indistinct conversations continue]

07:41.718 --> 07:44.286
I'm curious. Why do you
think you know what I want?

07:44.288 --> 07:47.154
I mean, it's a hard thing
to know even about oneself.

07:47.156 --> 07:50.725
I'm a stock picker and
an instinct trader.

07:50.727 --> 07:52.093
Am I wrong?

07:53.296 --> 07:54.796
[cellphone vibrates]

07:54.798 --> 07:56.263
Look.

07:56.265 --> 07:58.399
We believe there's a better way.

07:58.401 --> 08:01.736
Life doesn't have to be a zero-sum game.

08:01.738 --> 08:04.405
Go. Think.

08:04.407 --> 08:06.640
Let me know.

08:08.744 --> 08:11.778
[indistinct conversations]

08:18.488 --> 08:19.686
[birds chirping]

08:19.688 --> 08:21.454
<i>[Adam] Brownstone off the Promenade.</i>

08:21.456 --> 08:22.789
[door closes]

08:22.791 --> 08:24.457
Sometimes I forget which
caste you belong to, Chuck.

08:24.459 --> 08:25.692
Ah.

08:25.694 --> 08:27.895
This is a hell of a reminder.

08:27.897 --> 08:29.796
And where'd your dad
practice internal medicine?

08:29.798 --> 08:32.332
The rough side of Highland Park? Huh?

08:32.333 --> 08:35.869
I have to admit you surprise me,
even for a man in your position.

08:35.871 --> 08:37.303
There's not many who could cast a spell

08:37.304 --> 08:39.605
and make a federal judge disappear.

08:39.607 --> 08:42.607
There are no other men in my position.
[Chuckles]

08:42.610 --> 08:44.244
- [Adam chuckles]
- [chuckles]

08:44.246 --> 08:46.179
For I <i> also</i> know

08:46.181 --> 08:49.882
the name being nominated in
committee to replace Wilcox.

08:49.884 --> 08:51.151
Ah.

08:51.153 --> 08:54.887
And let me be the first
to congratulate you.

08:54.889 --> 08:57.056
Thank you.

08:57.058 --> 09:00.159
It's as it should be. You happy?
You <i> should</i> be happy.

09:00.161 --> 09:01.527
I'd be laughing like Hank Kingsley

09:01.529 --> 09:03.095
if I were in your Florsheims.

09:03.097 --> 09:04.329
- "Hey, now!"
- [ Laughs ]

09:04.331 --> 09:06.866
Hey, these are Ferragamos. [chuckles]

09:06.868 --> 09:08.768
I like to laugh, too.

09:08.770 --> 09:10.802
But lately...

09:10.804 --> 09:13.838
- Yes, lately.
- And I worry.

09:13.840 --> 09:16.241
With you out of the AG's office,

09:16.243 --> 09:18.410
she'll be even less
likely to look kindly

09:18.412 --> 09:19.878
on the work I need to do,

09:19.880 --> 09:21.313
especially when it diverges from...

09:21.315 --> 09:24.550
Whatever whim she and the
White House might have.

09:24.552 --> 09:25.850
Mm.

09:25.852 --> 09:28.186
I was wondering when the
actual tat would come.

09:28.188 --> 09:29.320
Or is this the tit?

09:29.322 --> 09:31.856
When it comes to picking
your replacement,

09:31.858 --> 09:34.960
I need someone who'll
look out for me in DC.

09:34.962 --> 09:37.629
So <i> you</i> wanna pick?

09:37.631 --> 09:41.265
I know a few likely candidates.

09:41.267 --> 09:44.402
I'll need <i> you</i> to foam the
runway for that replacement

09:44.404 --> 09:45.736
on your way out.

09:45.738 --> 09:48.372
Is this <i> really</i> still about Axelrod?

09:48.374 --> 09:50.374
What, he's that much of a
burr under your saddle?

09:50.376 --> 09:52.543
It's about justice.

09:52.545 --> 09:54.078
Of course.

09:56.616 --> 09:59.149
If, as you say, my name's
already been put forth,

09:59.151 --> 10:01.752
I'm not sure what
leverage you still have.

10:01.754 --> 10:04.187
I wanted to tell you this in person

10:04.189 --> 10:07.591
to see exactly how badly you want it.

10:07.593 --> 10:10.227
It would be brutal to
have it get this close

10:10.229 --> 10:11.862
only to stall in Judicial Committee.

10:11.864 --> 10:14.732
The Senate is so polarized these days.

10:14.734 --> 10:17.634
Judgeships get held hostage for...
[inhales deeply]

10:17.636 --> 10:19.436
months, years.

10:19.438 --> 10:21.371
Are you saying you can guarantee
I sail through committee?

10:21.373 --> 10:22.972
"Guarantee" is a word

10:22.974 --> 10:26.343
that amateurs use in politics.

10:26.345 --> 10:29.912
But I can make it so
that Senator Vandeveer

10:29.914 --> 10:34.017
takes you by the hand and
drags you to the bench.

10:34.019 --> 10:36.753
And what I have to do to get that done

10:36.755 --> 10:38.054
will not be pleasant.

10:38.056 --> 10:41.791
It'll be quite odious, so
I need your assurance.

10:47.098 --> 10:49.064
I'll do it.

10:49.066 --> 10:51.667
But about Axelrod and finding
a way to leg back in...

10:51.669 --> 10:53.135
- [sighs]
- Let... let me be

10:53.137 --> 10:54.770
General Bradley to your Patton

10:54.772 --> 10:57.005
and advise you to practice restraint.

10:57.007 --> 11:00.676
Ah. Oh, it was good advice
when Omar Bradley gave it.

11:00.678 --> 11:02.911
Safe.

11:02.913 --> 11:04.213
And one of them died

11:04.215 --> 11:06.514
a well-respected and admired general,

11:06.516 --> 11:08.349
and the other one died a legend.

11:08.351 --> 11:11.252
You name my pick for replacement.

11:11.254 --> 11:13.421
I'll lock in your appointment.

11:13.423 --> 11:17.159
And then I'll worry about
the rest from there.

11:17.161 --> 11:20.261
I won't lie. Having a
Michelin chef in house,

11:20.263 --> 11:23.164
it would be an excellent
recruiting tool.

11:23.166 --> 11:24.532
What do you think?

11:24.534 --> 11:26.033
Oh. It's a great kitchen.

11:26.035 --> 11:27.735
Love the La Cornue.

11:27.737 --> 11:30.004
But I would really miss,
you know, real people...

11:30.006 --> 11:33.241
"gastros" who light up when they
eat something really special.

11:33.243 --> 11:35.776
You go private serving
guys that might just have

11:35.778 --> 11:37.878
- ...whatever for lunch...
- [man] Mm.

11:37.880 --> 11:41.849
You could lead the effort
to expand our horizons.

11:41.851 --> 11:44.251
Don't let her off the hook, Lar.

11:44.253 --> 11:46.453
I won't. We'll talk soon.

11:46.455 --> 11:48.422
Yeah, thanks.

11:48.424 --> 11:49.957
[footsteps depart]

11:49.959 --> 11:51.726
You know, when people
ask you what you think,

11:51.728 --> 11:53.393
you don't really have to tell them.

11:53.395 --> 11:54.894
I could've said a lot more.

11:54.896 --> 11:56.062
[indistinct conversations]

11:56.064 --> 11:59.533
[Wags] Give him some fucking space!

11:59.535 --> 12:01.968
[Bobby exhales sharply]

12:01.970 --> 12:03.203
Give me a sec.

12:05.708 --> 12:06.806
Hey.

12:06.808 --> 12:08.208
[kiss]

12:08.210 --> 12:09.743
Something wrong?

12:09.745 --> 12:12.378
[smacks lips] Bad day.
Something happened.

12:12.380 --> 12:14.413
Something serious?

12:14.415 --> 12:16.916
I can't make it to Lilly's tonight.

12:16.918 --> 12:18.584
Really?

12:20.488 --> 12:22.889
What happened?

12:22.891 --> 12:24.124
[elevator bell dings,
footsteps approach]

12:24.126 --> 12:26.259
I blew a read.<i> Badly.</i>

12:26.261 --> 12:29.562
And I know the reason
wasn't in the numbers.

12:29.564 --> 12:32.365
It was in here. I'm gonna fix it.

12:33.601 --> 12:34.800
Wendy?

12:36.437 --> 12:37.803
I don't like it.

12:37.805 --> 12:40.005
This isn't three years ago, you know.

12:40.007 --> 12:43.008
She's at odds with you, with
herself, over this battle.

12:43.010 --> 12:44.442
You can't trust her.

12:44.444 --> 12:47.012
Well, she's the only one who can
give me what I need right now.

12:47.014 --> 12:48.881
[sighs]

12:48.883 --> 12:50.215
I know.

12:50.217 --> 12:52.184
<i>♪ pensive music ♪</i>

12:52.186 --> 12:54.119
She's gonna ask you about Donnie.

12:54.121 --> 12:58.223
<i>♪♪♪</i>

12:58.225 --> 13:00.025
[man] You new here?

13:00.027 --> 13:01.225
Maybe.

13:01.227 --> 13:03.227
Nice.

13:03.229 --> 13:07.031
Now all we need is a pole. [chuckles]

13:07.033 --> 13:08.833
<i>[Lu] I can't cook for a bunch of animals</i>

13:08.835 --> 13:11.303
who will eat anything, shit
on anything, fuck anything.

13:11.305 --> 13:13.672
Don't be ignorant. That's
just a stereotype.

13:13.674 --> 13:16.508
[engine revving]

13:16.510 --> 13:17.909
[tires squeal]

13:19.645 --> 13:22.213
- Okay, you hate the place. Fine.
- [vehicle departs rapidly]

13:22.215 --> 13:24.282
I was just trying to help
with your situation.

13:24.284 --> 13:25.416
Well, I wouldn't have a situation

13:25.418 --> 13:26.650
if it weren't for this place.

13:26.652 --> 13:28.152
Well, you probably wouldn't
have your own kitchen

13:28.154 --> 13:30.721
for another ten years either.

13:30.723 --> 13:32.156
Look, I'm sorry.

13:32.158 --> 13:33.724
But what happened to
my badass big sister

13:33.726 --> 13:35.592
who says what she wants and
doesn't waste two shits

13:35.594 --> 13:36.860
on what the world thinks of her?

13:36.862 --> 13:39.062
I'm right here in front of you.

13:39.064 --> 13:40.297
When's the last time you even hung out

13:40.299 --> 13:41.898
in the old neighborhood?

13:41.900 --> 13:43.500
What are we supposed to do,

13:43.502 --> 13:46.637
Go back to fucking McCrory's
and shoot pool with the guys?

13:48.574 --> 13:51.574
And the night takes shape.

13:51.576 --> 13:54.610
[indistinct conversations,
telephone rings in distance]

13:55.680 --> 13:57.280
So?

13:57.282 --> 13:58.748
- [Bryan] We break it down.
- [boxes thud]

13:58.750 --> 14:00.917
Put it in boxes.

14:00.919 --> 14:03.186
Well, this is where we get off, Dale.

14:03.188 --> 14:04.754
This tight little team can handle it.

14:04.756 --> 14:07.122
FBI doesn't do clerical?

14:07.124 --> 14:09.792
Not on this one. It's, uh, too sad.

14:09.794 --> 14:11.461
Yeah, since it's over,
I'm supposed to start on

14:11.463 --> 14:13.596
this synthetic marijuana
thing up in Orangeburg.

14:13.598 --> 14:15.231
Oh, it's not over.

14:15.233 --> 14:18.334
When it starts going back
into boxes, it's over.

14:18.336 --> 14:20.903
[indistinct conversations]

14:20.905 --> 14:24.406
[Ben] The FDA adverse reporting
database flagged 20 cases

14:24.408 --> 14:27.376
of acidosis associated
with similar SLGT2s.

14:27.378 --> 14:28.543
It was in the file.

14:28.545 --> 14:30.946
[Mafee] Yeah, we didn't fuck up. <i>He</i> did.

14:30.948 --> 14:33.648
[footsteps thudding]

14:35.486 --> 14:36.952
[knock on door]

14:36.954 --> 14:39.021
[door handle clicks,
indistinct conversations]

14:39.023 --> 14:41.055
- Hey.
- Hey.

14:43.026 --> 14:45.994
Hey, thanks for coming back.

14:45.996 --> 14:49.364
Hope you didn't get all the way home.

14:49.366 --> 14:50.766
Where were you?

14:52.369 --> 14:53.935
I'm here now.

14:58.441 --> 14:59.707
[door handle clicks]

14:59.709 --> 15:03.611
Hey, everybody, you can go home. Thanks.

15:03.613 --> 15:05.246
[door closes]

15:07.417 --> 15:10.952
I made a mistake today
that I shouldn't have.

15:10.954 --> 15:12.320
It could cost me a billion dollars

15:12.322 --> 15:14.254
after we've sifted through the wreckage.

15:14.256 --> 15:15.790
That's quite a mistake.

15:17.527 --> 15:19.727
I need an adjustment.

15:19.729 --> 15:22.062
You're finally ready for a real session.

15:22.064 --> 15:24.097
Yeah.

15:24.099 --> 15:25.866
If I talk it through with you,

15:25.868 --> 15:27.568
sharpen my focus,

15:27.570 --> 15:29.669
I'll be able to start
digging out tomorrow.

15:29.671 --> 15:31.438
- Tomorrow?
- Yeah, I already know

15:31.440 --> 15:34.741
the reason I made the
mistake was mental error.

15:34.743 --> 15:37.978
Now I just need to find out
why I wanted to make it.

15:40.715 --> 15:43.283
This might take a while.

15:45.120 --> 15:48.154
[Chuck sighing]

15:50.425 --> 15:52.191
- [dog food rattling]
- [clears throat]

15:52.193 --> 15:53.827
[front door opens]

15:53.829 --> 15:54.994
[door creaks]

15:54.996 --> 15:56.463
- [Chuck exhales sharply]
- Hey.

15:56.465 --> 15:57.831
- [bowl clatters]
- Carrie?

15:57.833 --> 15:59.833
- [door creaking]
- Uh...

15:59.835 --> 16:01.935
- [door closes]
- I was waiting for Wendy.

16:01.937 --> 16:03.936
Yeah, she called, said you
were both gonna be out.

16:03.938 --> 16:05.637
Yes, I have things to do.

16:05.639 --> 16:08.907
I thought she was in
with the kids tonight.

16:08.909 --> 16:11.377
[sighs] Must've gotten
our signals crossed.

16:11.379 --> 16:13.312
Her thing sounded kind of last-minute.

16:13.314 --> 16:15.647
[whispers] Okay.

16:15.649 --> 16:17.749
[exhales sharply]

16:19.219 --> 16:21.152
Must've had this on silent.

16:21.154 --> 16:23.254
Uh...

16:23.256 --> 16:24.990
the kids are already in their rooms.

16:24.992 --> 16:27.960
Eva's asleep. Kevin might
want another story.

16:27.962 --> 16:30.929
Uh... would you mind
cleaning up the dog food?

16:30.931 --> 16:32.731
Thank you.

16:32.733 --> 16:33.866
- [doorknob clicks]
- See you later.

16:33.868 --> 16:35.600
[door handle clicks, switch clicks]

16:40.240 --> 16:42.474
[bag thuds]

17:03.863 --> 17:06.163
[inhales and exhales deeply]

17:22.248 --> 17:24.515
Tell me about today.

17:24.517 --> 17:27.717
If you're successful enough,

17:27.719 --> 17:30.787
people think you can do anything,

17:30.789 --> 17:33.056
and then you start to believe it, too.

17:33.058 --> 17:35.425
You mean you do.

17:36.929 --> 17:39.529
I'm not Superman. That's what
I'm trying to get across.

17:39.531 --> 17:42.631
But today?

17:42.633 --> 17:45.634
I might've forgotten.

17:45.636 --> 17:49.004
It's hard not to engage in
a little magical thinking

17:49.006 --> 17:50.273
when everyone else is looking at you

17:50.275 --> 17:51.441
like you're some combination

17:51.443 --> 17:53.943
of Warren Buffet and God above.

17:53.945 --> 17:56.179
I don't buy that.

17:56.181 --> 17:59.782
Magical thinking is...
if I clean the house,

17:59.784 --> 18:02.718
then school gets canceled tomorrow.

18:02.720 --> 18:04.219
And this?

18:04.221 --> 18:07.990
I'm not wishing or guessing,
and I'm not usually wrong.

18:07.992 --> 18:09.892
And when you are, you take
your medicine and move on.

18:09.894 --> 18:11.827
It's what makes you great.

18:11.829 --> 18:14.329
But today, your own words,

18:14.331 --> 18:15.730
you missed something.

18:17.201 --> 18:20.535
Somehow the idea that all the guys...

18:20.537 --> 18:22.537
I asked Mafee,

18:22.539 --> 18:25.940
and the moment he said
that everyone else agreed

18:25.942 --> 18:30.112
that it was the wrong move,

18:30.114 --> 18:31.679
I had to stick it out,

18:31.681 --> 18:34.115
had to prove that I was
the difference maker.

18:34.117 --> 18:36.250
To who?

18:36.252 --> 18:38.185
Mafee? Danzig?

18:38.187 --> 18:39.453
Of course not.

18:39.455 --> 18:42.023
I agree. They all idolize you already.

18:42.025 --> 18:44.592
It wasn't about proving
anything to any of them.

18:47.563 --> 18:48.996
Look, you want me to fix

18:48.998 --> 18:51.064
the part of you that makes money.

18:51.066 --> 18:54.335
But it is attached to the rest, so...

18:54.337 --> 18:56.570
Like I said, this is gonna
take a little while.

18:59.775 --> 19:01.442
[Bryan] Why do I hate
these guys so much?

19:01.444 --> 19:04.678
- [object thuds]
- Well, they're criminals.

19:04.680 --> 19:06.913
And they're a lot richer than you.

19:09.785 --> 19:11.985
[sighs]

19:11.987 --> 19:15.288
<i>♪ pensive music ♪</i>

19:17.392 --> 19:19.492
Are we really doing what we're doing...

19:19.494 --> 19:23.129
- [papers rustle]
- ...for the reasons we say?

19:23.131 --> 19:26.599
Well, you mean, does making
these arrests, dealing fines,

19:26.601 --> 19:28.868
actually do anything
to keep markets fair?

19:28.870 --> 19:31.504
[papers rustling]

19:31.506 --> 19:33.273
[inhales deeply ] When
you put it like that...

19:33.275 --> 19:34.940
[sighs heavily]

19:34.942 --> 19:38.277
This kid I went to school with,

19:38.279 --> 19:39.712
Jim Gagne...

19:39.714 --> 19:42.081
most brilliant guy I've ever met.

19:42.083 --> 19:43.949
Gagne was a double major

19:43.951 --> 19:46.852
in chemical engineering and pre-med.

19:46.854 --> 19:49.221
I felt like he was gonna cure cancer.

19:49.223 --> 19:52.558
Well, cancer's still
going last I checked.

19:52.560 --> 19:54.326
He's no scientist.

19:54.328 --> 19:57.629
He works the medical
sector for Spartan-Ives,

19:57.631 --> 19:59.231
made 20 million last year.

19:59.233 --> 20:02.634
Society's fucked when that happens.

20:02.636 --> 20:04.236
Incentives all out of whack.

20:04.238 --> 20:07.606
So someone has to do something.

20:07.608 --> 20:11.976
And we use laws and fines and jail.

20:11.978 --> 20:13.277
We try.

20:13.279 --> 20:14.512
<i>♪♪♪</i>

20:14.514 --> 20:16.480
- [ice rattles]
- [sips]

20:16.482 --> 20:18.917
- [Bryan inhales deeply]
- [envelope rustles]

20:18.919 --> 20:22.420
Got this made 'cause I was
so fucking proud of Chuck

20:22.422 --> 20:24.756
for pushing back.

20:24.758 --> 20:26.224
<i>♪♪♪</i>

20:26.226 --> 20:27.925
[glass clinks]

20:27.927 --> 20:30.728
It's Axe's settlement check,
but I forgot to give it to him

20:30.730 --> 20:32.697
by the time it came
back from the framer,

20:32.699 --> 20:35.032
with the, uh, Donnie of it all.

20:35.034 --> 20:37.968
I'm gonna leave it on his desk.

20:37.970 --> 20:40.371
[chuckles]

20:40.373 --> 20:41.539
[envelope thuds]

20:41.541 --> 20:43.073
<i>♪♪♪</i>

20:43.075 --> 20:45.075
[bottle clinks]

20:45.077 --> 20:46.576
[papers rustle]

20:46.578 --> 20:48.746
I know where Chuck keeps his stash.

20:48.748 --> 20:50.413
[footsteps depart]

20:50.415 --> 20:53.183
Come on.

20:53.185 --> 20:54.584
[Kate] Sounds dangerous.

20:54.586 --> 20:57.621
Let's talk about you for a sec.

20:57.623 --> 21:00.590
That's not how this works.

21:00.592 --> 21:03.025
We've never done anything
the way it works,

21:03.027 --> 21:05.662
and we're not exactly starting tonight.

21:05.664 --> 21:07.731
How are you handling everything?

21:09.635 --> 21:12.469
I wanna know before we go on.

21:12.471 --> 21:16.205
Grant me this indulgence.

21:17.842 --> 21:19.909
[clicks teeth]

21:19.911 --> 21:22.544
The Donnie thing threw me, to be honest.

21:24.548 --> 21:29.418
There's an empty space in
the world without him.

21:29.420 --> 21:31.954
The fact that...

21:31.956 --> 21:34.323
I missed it.

21:34.325 --> 21:35.824
This man, this...

21:35.826 --> 21:39.628
patient of mine, dying.

21:39.630 --> 21:41.129
And he wouldn't let me in,

21:41.131 --> 21:43.865
despite whatever was going on with him.

21:43.867 --> 21:45.668
And you.

21:45.670 --> 21:49.404
People withhold crucial
information all the time.

21:50.640 --> 21:52.874
We learn to manage our expectations

21:52.876 --> 21:54.910
about those close to us, don't we?

21:54.912 --> 21:58.479
So they don't turn into mistrust or...

21:58.481 --> 22:01.116
paranoia.

22:01.118 --> 22:02.750
When I was young, I figured if I was

22:02.752 --> 22:05.820
truly there for my patients,

22:05.822 --> 22:09.524
I could get them to be
truly open with me.

22:09.526 --> 22:12.026
I quickly learned that's not
the case, but you still hope.

22:12.028 --> 22:13.361
- Really?
- [fist thuds]

22:13.363 --> 22:15.496
That's what you were thinking
about when you were young?

22:15.498 --> 22:18.333
Fuck. You chose the right line of work.

22:18.335 --> 22:19.600
[chuckles]

22:19.602 --> 22:22.502
I was just thinking about
getting rich and getting even.

22:22.504 --> 22:23.737
Have you?

22:23.739 --> 22:25.439
Yeah. Mostly.

22:25.441 --> 22:27.741
Does it make everything all better?

22:27.743 --> 22:29.343
Why doesn't it?

22:29.345 --> 22:32.813
Because the world isn't simple.

22:32.815 --> 22:35.015
Like with Donnie.

22:35.017 --> 22:37.084
You keep going back there.

22:37.086 --> 22:40.354
I don't think we can ignore
that you missed today,

22:40.356 --> 22:43.523
for the first time in
forever, right after he died.

22:43.525 --> 22:46.226
Okay, go ahead, doctor.
You connect those dots.

22:46.228 --> 22:49.295
- Well, you used the words.
- [clink]

22:49.297 --> 22:51.431
Getting even.

22:51.433 --> 22:54.501
- When I was a kid.
- And today?

22:54.503 --> 22:55.735
Bombing the trade,

22:55.737 --> 22:57.937
were you somehow evening
the score for Donnie?

22:57.939 --> 23:02.441
What does that even mean?
Donnie was a friend.

23:02.443 --> 23:05.044
Everyone here matters to me,

23:05.046 --> 23:07.180
and I go out of my way for all of 'em.

23:07.182 --> 23:10.516
That's why I got him
the best medical care.

23:10.518 --> 23:13.185
The same as when Mick Danzig
gets tackled on his lawn

23:13.187 --> 23:17.055
with a machine gun in his fucking hands,

23:17.057 --> 23:19.358
I'm the one who pays off the cops

23:19.360 --> 23:21.059
to make the problem go away.

23:21.061 --> 23:24.597
That's what I do here.

23:24.599 --> 23:27.199
I take care of my people,

23:27.201 --> 23:29.801
and they know that.

23:29.803 --> 23:31.770
And so should you by now.

23:31.772 --> 23:34.306
[inhales deeply]

23:35.675 --> 23:37.009
So are you ready to tell me

23:37.011 --> 23:38.743
who you were trying to
prove something to?

23:40.480 --> 23:42.881
Yeah.

23:42.883 --> 23:45.116
Should we say it in unison?

23:45.118 --> 23:46.918
And were you trying to prove

23:46.920 --> 23:50.221
you were a difference
maker for good or bad?

23:50.223 --> 23:53.525
Were you trying to reward
or punish yourself?

23:55.762 --> 23:57.796
[whispers] Come on.

23:57.798 --> 23:59.130
Where you going?

24:01.100 --> 24:03.367
- [Wendy] We're not done!
- Come on!

24:05.905 --> 24:07.838
[sighs]

24:07.840 --> 24:10.841
[Lu] God, that was awful. [laughs]

24:10.843 --> 24:12.109
You don't even go there anymore.

24:12.111 --> 24:13.277
You're a Michelin chef.

24:13.279 --> 24:14.578
You live in Bushwick with the hipsters.

24:14.580 --> 24:15.879
The only reason we ever went there

24:15.881 --> 24:17.048
is 'cause they didn't check IDs.

24:17.050 --> 24:19.483
[laughs] God! What were you thinking?

24:19.485 --> 24:21.985
I just... I thought we could
do something like we used to,

24:21.987 --> 24:24.788
before everything was all
work and you were all...

24:24.790 --> 24:28.158
Then let's do something. Better.

24:28.160 --> 24:29.693
Where else did we used to go?

24:29.695 --> 24:31.361
Nowhere I wanna go now.

24:31.363 --> 24:33.997
- [Lu] After you got your car...
- Oh, that fucking Fiero.

24:33.999 --> 24:38.068
Man, we'd just drive around, joyriding.

24:38.070 --> 24:39.836
Then let's go joyriding.

24:39.838 --> 24:43.073
Come on. Come on! Come on.

24:43.075 --> 24:45.008
[laughter]

24:45.010 --> 24:47.610
[vehicles passing]

24:47.612 --> 24:50.713
I thought I might not see
you here for a while.

24:50.715 --> 24:54.484
[clicks teeth] Well, I may have been...

24:54.486 --> 24:56.452
overly harsh with you before.

24:56.454 --> 24:59.589
"Overly harsh"?

24:59.591 --> 25:01.757
I don't know. I'm...

25:01.759 --> 25:04.360
I'm getting up there in years.

25:04.362 --> 25:05.661
I don't really, uh,

25:05.663 --> 25:09.298
understand these things anymore.

25:09.300 --> 25:11.433
I don't even know why you're here.

25:13.004 --> 25:16.905
There is a favor I need.

25:16.907 --> 25:19.308
Ah...

25:19.310 --> 25:21.210
Now we get to it.

25:24.047 --> 25:25.814
What can I help you with?

25:25.816 --> 25:28.182
I need a Senator

25:28.184 --> 25:30.118
on the judiciary committee

25:30.120 --> 25:33.354
to push through a nomination.

25:33.356 --> 25:35.690
<i>Your</i> Senator.

25:35.692 --> 25:38.693
And I'm supposed to just...

25:38.695 --> 25:41.996
materialize Marcia Vandeveer?

25:41.998 --> 25:44.832
A United States Senator?

25:44.834 --> 25:47.268
<i>And</i> get her to do what you want?

25:47.270 --> 25:48.469
I know that you and Marcia...

25:48.471 --> 25:49.970
I must still know how the game works

25:49.972 --> 25:52.773
to be able to do something like that.

25:52.775 --> 25:56.677
- [siren wailing in distance]
- I must've spent a lifetime

25:56.679 --> 26:00.047
building relationships,

26:00.049 --> 26:01.615
collecting chits.

26:01.617 --> 26:03.984
Whatever law and order issue
that she's running on,

26:03.986 --> 26:07.655
my office will make it a priority.

26:09.191 --> 26:10.824
Accommodations will not be necessary,

26:10.826 --> 26:13.193
not necessary at all.

26:13.195 --> 26:15.762
She owes me a favor.

26:15.764 --> 26:18.365
She'll be happy to sit with you.
I'll just give her a call.

26:18.367 --> 26:20.700
Well...

26:20.702 --> 26:22.536
as long as it's not too much trouble.

26:26.741 --> 26:28.975
Anything you'd like to say to me?

26:28.977 --> 26:31.410
Thank you, Dad.

26:33.915 --> 26:35.548
And?

26:39.788 --> 26:41.621
I'm sorry. [Sighs]

26:43.291 --> 26:45.758
[inhales deeply] There's the boy.

26:48.129 --> 26:49.861
[sniffs]

26:49.863 --> 26:51.029
<i>[Van Halen's "And the
Cradle Will Rock" playing]</i>

26:51.031 --> 26:52.965
- [object clatters]
- [Bobby] No.

26:54.469 --> 26:57.336
- [object thuds]
- [Wendy laughs]

26:57.338 --> 26:58.804
<i>♪ Oh, yeah ♪</i>

26:58.806 --> 27:00.573
<i>- ♪ Get up ♪</i> - [Bobby] Whoa!

27:01.675 --> 27:02.841
<i>♪ Ow! ♪</i>

27:02.843 --> 27:05.210
[object thuds loudly]
- Oh! Unbelievable!

27:05.212 --> 27:07.378
I'd have given 30 to one odds
you'd miss with the phone.

27:07.380 --> 27:09.982
Then you're definitely
not seeing the market.

27:09.984 --> 27:11.149
I can do a phone.

27:11.151 --> 27:12.450
It's gotta be bigger than a phone now.

27:12.452 --> 27:14.152
<i>♪ Well, they say it's kinda frightnin' ♪</i>

27:14.154 --> 27:16.454
<i>♪ How this younger generation swings ♪</i>

27:16.456 --> 27:20.958
<i>♪ You know, it's more than
just some new sensation ♪</i>

27:20.960 --> 27:23.228
<i>♪ Well, the kid is into losin' sleep ♪</i>

27:23.230 --> 27:25.263
<i>♪ And he don't come home
for half the week ♪</i>

27:25.265 --> 27:26.731
[loud crash]

27:26.733 --> 27:29.501
<i>♪ You know it's more than
just an aggravation ♪</i>

27:29.503 --> 27:32.737
<i>- ♪ And the cradle ♪</i> - [laughing]

27:32.739 --> 27:34.139
Do you remember our first building?

27:34.141 --> 27:37.975
Ooh! Globe would've
gone through the floor.

27:37.977 --> 27:40.344
Okay, double or nothing.
I wanna do a computer.

27:40.346 --> 27:41.746
Oh, my God. You're like
Kobe firing up shots

27:41.748 --> 27:42.980
when he's two for 18.

27:42.982 --> 27:44.982
No doubt in your mind the
next one's going in.

27:44.984 --> 27:47.785
Kobe? Steph Curry. Jordan, maybe.

27:47.787 --> 27:48.953
Don't give me <i> Kobe.</i>

27:48.955 --> 27:50.821
Shooter's gotta shoot.

27:50.823 --> 27:53.056
Unwavering belief in
our own capabilities.

27:53.058 --> 27:54.858
It's essential to a point.

27:54.860 --> 27:56.726
Keeps us functioning at a high level.

27:56.728 --> 27:58.328
Until it isn't, right?

27:58.330 --> 28:01.331
Maybe your self-image is creating...

28:01.333 --> 28:02.533
a blind spot.

28:04.303 --> 28:06.036
We're not on a break, are we?

28:06.038 --> 28:07.271
No.

28:09.474 --> 28:11.407
Why couldn't I have seen it before?

28:11.409 --> 28:13.009
Well, let's assume your blind spot

28:13.011 --> 28:15.244
usually works for you.

28:15.246 --> 28:17.346
It's fairly essentially
if you don't feel

28:17.348 --> 28:18.648
indestructible like Superman.

28:18.650 --> 28:20.817
How are you gonna risk
billions every morning?

28:20.819 --> 28:22.852
But it's not working for you now.

28:22.854 --> 28:24.020
So you need to figure out

28:24.022 --> 28:25.854
what part of your self-image is false.

28:25.856 --> 28:27.990
And then you either need to
live up to it or lose it.

28:27.992 --> 28:32.195
Interesting word... "false." Like, uh...

28:32.197 --> 28:35.130
when someone knows that they
have to tell a lover goodbye.

28:35.132 --> 28:36.499
But they can't quite do it,

28:36.501 --> 28:39.268
so instead, they sleep
with them one last time.

28:39.270 --> 28:41.103
Then they have their
own unspoken goodbye,

28:41.105 --> 28:44.707
not letting on that
everything's changed until...

28:44.709 --> 28:46.241
after the night is over.

28:46.243 --> 28:48.210
[exhales]

28:48.212 --> 28:51.479
I'm not sure that's what
we're discussing here.

28:51.481 --> 28:53.148
No, maybe not.

28:53.150 --> 28:54.649
But it came to mind, so I said it.

28:54.651 --> 28:56.318
Isn't that what I'm supposed to do?

28:57.922 --> 28:59.588
In a sense.

28:59.590 --> 29:01.355
[footsteps thud]

29:01.357 --> 29:03.090
Something I said?

29:03.092 --> 29:04.958
Let's go outside.

29:04.960 --> 29:06.694
[footsteps depart]

29:06.696 --> 29:08.295
[lock clicking]

29:08.297 --> 29:10.731
- Mm.
- [glasses clink]

29:10.733 --> 29:12.466
[kiss]

29:12.468 --> 29:14.468
<i>♪ tense music ♪</i>

29:14.470 --> 29:16.670
[breathing heavily]

29:16.672 --> 29:18.805
[objects thud]

29:18.807 --> 29:21.908
<i>♪♪♪</i>

29:21.910 --> 29:23.944
[jacket rustles]

29:23.946 --> 29:26.980
[laughing]

29:28.884 --> 29:31.551
[both laughing]

29:31.553 --> 29:33.353
- Sorry, that was...
- So cliché. [Laughing]

29:33.355 --> 29:36.021
Oh, the worst! [Laughs]

29:36.023 --> 29:38.491
Oh. You think Chuck's ever had sex here?

29:38.493 --> 29:40.860
- Oh, time to leave right now.
- Ohh. Oh, God. [Laughs]

29:40.862 --> 29:45.365
- [Bryan laughing]
- Oh! [Laughs]

29:45.367 --> 29:47.166
- Oh.
- Oh.

29:47.168 --> 29:49.469
I still wanna do something dangerous.

29:51.672 --> 29:53.338
- [horn honks]
- Hey, Nancy. Church Rhoades.

29:53.340 --> 29:54.940
Looking for Wendy.

29:54.942 --> 29:57.709
Wondering if you knew
what she was up to.

29:57.711 --> 30:00.012
Maybe her phone died.

30:00.014 --> 30:04.150
Uh, anyway, when you get this,
let me know if you know. Thanks.

30:04.152 --> 30:05.651
[horn honks]

30:05.653 --> 30:07.419
[exhales deeply]

30:07.421 --> 30:09.421
[laughter]

30:09.423 --> 30:13.492
[ambient music playing
over loudspeakers]

30:13.494 --> 30:15.093
♪♪♪

30:15.095 --> 30:17.362
[Ira] We'll have, uh, another Bulleit.

30:17.364 --> 30:18.630
All right, same thing.

30:18.632 --> 30:21.633
Splash of soda and, uh, little,
uh, little lemon zest.

30:21.635 --> 30:22.934
Oh! Will you bring us two?

30:22.936 --> 30:24.202
[woman] For sure.

30:24.204 --> 30:26.070
I was beginning to think
you were a no-show.

30:26.072 --> 30:30.508
I'm beginning to wish I no-showed.

30:30.510 --> 30:32.076
I don't see the appeal.

30:32.078 --> 30:34.512
♪♪♪

30:34.514 --> 30:35.880
[cellphone touchscreen clicking]

30:35.882 --> 30:37.081
See it now?

30:37.083 --> 30:39.850
Oh, Christ. Ira.

30:39.852 --> 30:41.819
Don't make indict you for child porn.

30:41.821 --> 30:44.154
She's of age. She just sent that to me.

30:44.156 --> 30:45.790
God bless these 23-year-olds.

30:45.792 --> 30:46.924
They grew up with porn.

30:46.926 --> 30:49.059
- [scoffs]
- And daddy issues.

30:49.061 --> 30:50.695
Maybe granddaddy issues in your case.

30:50.697 --> 30:52.996
- Ow.
- [chuckles]

30:52.998 --> 30:55.366
What do you talk to a 23-year-old about?

30:55.368 --> 30:57.167
Taylor Swift?

30:57.169 --> 30:58.401
Did you meet her on Tinder?

30:58.403 --> 31:00.570
Actually, I did. [laughing]

31:00.572 --> 31:03.707
How do you do it? I mean, get 'em to...

31:03.709 --> 31:06.376
swipe left or right or
whatever on a mug like yours.

31:06.378 --> 31:07.945
You put the Porsche in the Tinder photo.

31:07.947 --> 31:09.079
[scoffs]

31:09.081 --> 31:10.981
You can't be subtle on Tinder.

31:10.983 --> 31:12.282
- Mm. Thank you.
- Wow.

31:12.284 --> 31:14.250
Mm-hmm.

31:14.252 --> 31:15.618
- How'd it go?
- [clears throat]

31:15.620 --> 31:17.119
Not as bad as you thought, I'm sure.

31:17.121 --> 31:18.355
- Mm.
- [ice rattling]

31:18.357 --> 31:20.557
Worse, I think.

31:20.559 --> 31:22.392
I believe that he used "I told you so"

31:22.394 --> 31:24.260
in all its myriad constructions.

31:24.262 --> 31:26.162
- [sets down glass]
- I understand how it must

31:26.164 --> 31:28.898
make you feel to have to
ask for a favor like that.

31:28.900 --> 31:32.969
But everyone has a roof. Accept it.

31:32.971 --> 31:34.503
[smacks lips] A roof?

31:34.505 --> 31:36.172
Those two years I was in Russia,

31:36.174 --> 31:37.773
it was right after the wall came down.

31:37.775 --> 31:40.709
There was money and crazy women.

31:40.711 --> 31:42.411
The Wild West of capitalism.

31:42.413 --> 31:45.681
Anyway, in Russia, you had to
pay someone to protect you,

31:45.683 --> 31:48.083
either the cops or the mob, and
then they were your "roof."

31:48.085 --> 31:51.353
- Mm.
- That's what they called it.

31:51.355 --> 31:53.088
You're down right now. It's
not a moment for pride.

31:53.090 --> 31:55.991
It's a moment for, uh...

31:55.993 --> 31:57.593
consolidation.

31:57.595 --> 32:00.729
Positioning, a little security.
Senior's your roof.

32:00.731 --> 32:03.098
- Everyone needs a roof.
- I may need one.

32:03.100 --> 32:05.100
It doesn't mean I have
to fucking like it.

32:05.102 --> 32:06.768
Yeah, but if you don't have a roof,

32:06.770 --> 32:08.870
you can't be surprised when
it starts raining on you.

32:08.872 --> 32:10.772
Well, it's like the man sang,

32:10.774 --> 32:13.341
"it may be the devil
or it may be the Lord,

32:13.343 --> 32:16.544
but you're gonna have to
serve somebody," right?

32:16.546 --> 32:18.213
- [footsteps approach]
- [woman] Hey.

32:18.215 --> 32:20.114
Hi.

32:20.116 --> 32:22.149
[whispering indistinctly]

32:22.151 --> 32:23.918
[whispers] Think about that.

32:23.920 --> 32:25.420
- All right.
- [woman] Mm-hmm.

32:25.422 --> 32:27.422
Tyler, go to the bar. I'll...
I'll find you later.

32:27.424 --> 32:29.223
[Tyler] Okay.

32:29.225 --> 32:33.294
How are you able to keep
it so light, brother?

32:33.296 --> 32:35.930
In law school, you were just as
weighted down as the rest of us.

32:35.932 --> 32:38.198
Light. Heavy.

32:38.200 --> 32:40.534
- Who even thinks in those terms?
- Mm-hmm.

32:40.536 --> 32:41.668
Weekends and on Wednesdays,

32:41.670 --> 32:43.037
I'm with my kids and I'm one way.

32:43.039 --> 32:45.605
And when I'm not, I'm here,
or somewhere like it.

32:45.607 --> 32:47.808
Otherwise, what? Watch
harness racing on TV?

32:47.810 --> 32:50.311
No, you should know that that's rigged.

32:50.313 --> 32:51.478
They can shift the results

32:51.480 --> 32:52.779
just by dinging one wheel of the sulky.

32:52.781 --> 32:54.781
I don't actually bet
the fucking trotters.

32:54.783 --> 32:56.149
- Where are you, fella?
- [scoffs]

32:56.151 --> 32:57.484
'Cause you're not here.

32:57.486 --> 32:58.885
It's one thing if I check my phone.

32:58.887 --> 33:00.754
Could be some girl telling
me she just turned 21.

33:00.756 --> 33:02.255
What the fuck are you doing?

33:02.257 --> 33:03.423
♪♪♪

33:03.425 --> 33:05.959
Wendy.

33:05.961 --> 33:07.226
I don't... [sighs]

33:07.228 --> 33:09.795
[hip-hop music playing
over loudspeakers]

33:09.797 --> 33:12.966
I'm not sure where she is tonight.

33:12.968 --> 33:15.601
Ah.

33:15.603 --> 33:17.370
- Fuck.
- Yeah.

33:17.372 --> 33:19.272
And, uh, it doesn't feel like

33:19.274 --> 33:22.942
a "we're just out of
pocket for a minute."

33:22.944 --> 33:26.111
There's some kind of
continental drift going on.

33:26.113 --> 33:28.447
Worse.

33:28.449 --> 33:30.883
Tectonic collisions.

33:30.885 --> 33:33.819
♪♪♪

33:33.821 --> 33:36.154
You know, no offense, man, but...

33:36.156 --> 33:39.592
all of this is not for me.

33:39.594 --> 33:41.793
So it scares the shit out of me

33:41.795 --> 33:43.362
that it could be where I'm heading.

33:43.364 --> 33:47.565
♪♪♪

33:47.567 --> 33:49.601
[exhales sharply] It's
not really for anyone,

33:49.603 --> 33:52.904
tell you the truth.

33:52.906 --> 33:54.272
No one chooses it.

33:54.274 --> 33:57.009
Even if they think they do
when they walk out the door.

33:57.011 --> 34:00.444
it's... not what they think it'll be,

34:00.446 --> 34:02.514
especially after the first few months.

34:02.516 --> 34:03.882
♪♪♪

34:03.884 --> 34:06.518
Everything I said to you about
the young girls is true.

34:06.520 --> 34:09.152
They're wild and free and...

34:09.155 --> 34:11.322
they'll lick your dirty
places and smile.

34:11.324 --> 34:14.992
But the one thing they are not is...

34:14.994 --> 34:17.395
my Elizabeth.

34:17.397 --> 34:18.661
Or Wendy.

34:18.664 --> 34:20.697
<i>♪♪♪</i>

34:20.699 --> 34:23.134
I know.

34:23.136 --> 34:27.170
I remember nights with
Liz, and she'd be asleep,

34:27.172 --> 34:30.341
and I'd have all these things
that I'd wanna tell her.

34:30.342 --> 34:32.509
Then I wouldn't wake her up.
I'd just sit with it.

34:32.511 --> 34:35.277
And...

34:35.280 --> 34:37.414
by morning, they'd be gone. [Sighs]

34:37.416 --> 34:41.484
Plowed under with the routine.

34:41.485 --> 34:44.755
If I could get one of
those nights back...

34:44.757 --> 34:48.724
I'm not saying I'd give up
all these nights, but, uh...

34:48.726 --> 34:52.295
[footsteps approach]

34:52.297 --> 34:55.231
Yeah, I probably have a few
things like that I should say.

34:55.233 --> 34:57.267
Then why the fuck are you
still sitting here with me?

34:57.269 --> 34:58.734
[exhales sharply]

34:58.736 --> 35:02.738
'Cause one thing's for sure,
you got absolutely no game.

35:02.740 --> 35:03.906
[chuckles]

35:05.777 --> 35:08.243
I never cried over Donnie, you know.

35:10.748 --> 35:13.015
You wanted to?

35:13.017 --> 35:15.585
I think I should have, maybe.

35:15.587 --> 35:17.553
Last time you did?

35:17.555 --> 35:20.022
- Oh, I don't know.
- Sure you do.

35:21.492 --> 35:23.425
Let's turn here.

35:23.427 --> 35:26.861
I like to wander from time to time.

35:26.863 --> 35:30.732
It's our little expeditions
that keep me around.

35:30.734 --> 35:32.934
Digging in the dirt,
getting under the process.

35:32.936 --> 35:36.572
But I was supposed to be home hours ago.

35:36.574 --> 35:38.673
Last time you cried.

35:41.612 --> 35:45.046
Fuck. Okay.

35:45.048 --> 35:47.582
You know what really nails me?

35:49.786 --> 35:52.954
These YouTube videos,
soldiers coming home,

35:52.956 --> 35:55.756
surprising their kids at school.

35:55.758 --> 35:59.427
Even better... baseball game.

35:59.429 --> 36:01.795
So the guy subs for the catcher.

36:01.797 --> 36:04.565
Kid goes to the mound,
he gets ready to pitch.

36:04.567 --> 36:07.368
He throws one. He hasn't noticed.

36:07.370 --> 36:09.937
And the catcher goes to the mound,

36:09.939 --> 36:12.606
takes off his mask, kid sees him,

36:12.608 --> 36:17.044
and the dad just wraps him in a hug.

36:17.046 --> 36:19.747
I have no idea why, but if I
stumble across one of those,

36:19.749 --> 36:22.315
I am <i> gone.</i>

36:22.317 --> 36:25.185
Does it feel good after?

36:25.187 --> 36:27.887
Yeah, it does.

36:27.889 --> 36:31.724
Jesus. Nobody knows that, not even Lara.

36:31.726 --> 36:34.628
It's okay for that to be private.

36:34.630 --> 36:36.263
Do you know what's going on?

36:36.265 --> 36:37.397
You're not gonna tell me

36:37.399 --> 36:39.199
it's because my dad never came home?

36:39.201 --> 36:40.700
Well, I think that might be in there,

36:40.702 --> 36:44.904
but I think we resolved a bunch of that.

36:44.906 --> 36:48.141
No, I think about the mask itself.

36:48.143 --> 36:50.276
I think about what it means that
the dad pulls off the mask,

36:50.278 --> 36:54.346
and he's not only seen
but loved for who he is

36:54.348 --> 36:58.517
underneath that hard metal exterior.

36:58.519 --> 37:03.055
Well, that guy's a hero.
He deserves the love.

37:03.057 --> 37:04.456
And you?

37:09.129 --> 37:10.996
What happens when you take it off?

37:13.367 --> 37:16.134
Will you still be loved?

37:16.136 --> 37:18.836
By the guys here, your kids, Lara?

37:18.838 --> 37:21.906
What if you're not perfect?

37:21.908 --> 37:24.175
What if you miss one every few years?

37:24.177 --> 37:26.911
Yeah.

37:26.913 --> 37:29.614
What then?

37:29.616 --> 37:32.617
<i>♪ pensive music ♪</i>

37:32.619 --> 37:34.351
Let's stay with Donnie a minute more.

37:34.353 --> 37:38.355
<i>♪♪♪</i>

37:38.357 --> 37:41.826
<i>[The Hold Steady] ♪
Subpoenaed in Texas ♪</i>

37:41.828 --> 37:44.428
<i>♪ Sequestered in Memphis ♪</i>

37:44.430 --> 37:46.597
It's not the same without the Fiero.

37:46.599 --> 37:49.433
Yeah. Can't feel the road in this.

37:49.435 --> 37:52.035
And you can't hear the fucking engine.

37:52.037 --> 37:54.104
Are we going somewhere?

37:54.106 --> 37:56.940
Nah.

37:56.942 --> 37:58.242
We're just gonna joyride.

37:58.244 --> 37:59.643
<i>♪♪♪</i>

37:59.645 --> 38:03.347
<i>♪ I think she drove a new Mustang ♪</i>

38:03.349 --> 38:05.115
<i>♪ I guess it might be a rental ♪</i>

38:05.117 --> 38:06.816
- No.
- [helicopter blades whirring]

38:06.818 --> 38:10.419
<i>♪ I remember she had satellite radio ♪</i>

38:10.421 --> 38:12.355
<i>♪ I guess she seemed a bit nervous ♪</i>

38:12.357 --> 38:14.991
<i>♪ Do you think I'm that stupid? ♪</i>

38:14.993 --> 38:16.659
- Are you ready?
- Yeah.

38:16.661 --> 38:18.094
Oh, my God.

38:18.096 --> 38:19.729
Fuck, yeah.

38:19.731 --> 38:21.998
[helicopter blades whirring]

38:22.000 --> 38:23.733
[beer sloshes]

38:23.735 --> 38:26.502
You know, I think you're
right about me, Lu.

38:26.504 --> 38:29.872
I'm not your ballsy big sister
who doesn't give two shits.

38:29.874 --> 38:31.807
The old me would've told
Bobby to go fuck himself

38:31.809 --> 38:34.677
for blowing me off to talk
to Wendy Rhoades all night.

38:34.679 --> 38:36.612
So why didn't you?

38:36.614 --> 38:39.782
Because I'm different than who I was.

38:39.784 --> 38:42.818
Improved, supposedly.

38:42.820 --> 38:45.087
You didn't need that kind of improving.

38:47.191 --> 38:49.357
I do need something, though.

38:52.296 --> 38:55.397
What?

38:55.399 --> 38:57.198
What do you want?

38:57.200 --> 39:00.168
[helicopter blades continue whirring]

39:02.939 --> 39:04.738
I tell you,

39:04.740 --> 39:07.141
this beats hitting the mall
and shoplifting earrings.

39:07.143 --> 39:09.677
- Mm.
- [chuckles]

39:09.679 --> 39:13.514
God, we'd always end up
at that stupid mall.

39:13.516 --> 39:16.150
Remember when Mom
bought us scratch-offs,

39:16.152 --> 39:18.051
and we agreed if either of us won,

39:18.053 --> 39:19.252
we'd go on a shopping spree?

39:19.254 --> 39:20.454
Yeah.

39:20.456 --> 39:22.189
You kind of won.

39:27.663 --> 39:30.030
We've now gone as far as we possible can

39:30.032 --> 39:31.932
without getting to it.

39:31.934 --> 39:36.569
[crickets chirping]

39:36.571 --> 39:37.971
Donnie.

39:40.309 --> 39:43.276
Fine. Donnie.

39:43.278 --> 39:45.345
But first, tell me what
you've put together.

39:45.347 --> 39:48.514
I know you used him as a shield.

39:48.516 --> 39:51.751
I don't know how exactly.

39:51.753 --> 39:54.286
And I know you left his
family well off afterwards.

39:54.288 --> 39:56.288
That's all true.

39:57.826 --> 40:00.827
So you should feel great.

40:00.829 --> 40:03.529
You saved your kingdom

40:03.531 --> 40:05.965
and rewarded richly the
knight who fell on his sword

40:05.967 --> 40:07.199
so you could do it.

40:07.201 --> 40:09.869
A king who does not mourn that knight

40:09.871 --> 40:13.339
and that goes on
building his own castle.

40:13.341 --> 40:17.343
Oh, so that's why you
missed on the trade.

40:17.345 --> 40:18.844
You loved him,

40:18.846 --> 40:20.880
so subconsciously, you're
punishing yourself.

40:24.785 --> 40:26.752
I stole from him.

40:26.754 --> 40:29.120
<i>♪ pensive music ♪</i>

40:29.122 --> 40:31.857
His time,

40:31.859 --> 40:33.725
Without his permission.

40:33.727 --> 40:36.695
Doctor presented me with
a chance to get Donnie

40:36.697 --> 40:39.731
some experimental treatment, not a cure.

40:39.733 --> 40:41.599
<i>♪♪♪</i>

40:41.601 --> 40:46.271
But it could've extended his life a...
few months...

40:46.273 --> 40:47.972
<i>♪♪♪</i>

40:47.974 --> 40:51.675
and maybe long enough for
him to have seen Christmas.

40:53.713 --> 40:58.348
But also maybe long enough for
him to testify against me.

40:58.350 --> 41:01.184
And...

41:01.186 --> 41:02.520
I stopped that from happening

41:02.522 --> 41:04.988
because it didn't suit my purposes.

41:04.990 --> 41:06.457
And I'm punishing myself

41:06.459 --> 41:09.159
because I cannot believe
I have the capacity

41:09.161 --> 41:12.162
to do that to someone I care about.

41:12.164 --> 41:14.664
<i>♪♪♪</i>

41:14.666 --> 41:18.268
That's your fear?

41:18.270 --> 41:20.003
That even when you care about someone,

41:20.005 --> 41:21.638
you can use them for your own ends.

41:21.640 --> 41:24.041
If that is true, I don't
like what it says about me.

41:24.043 --> 41:25.976
It may be true,

41:25.978 --> 41:28.312
but that's not what this is.

41:28.314 --> 41:31.714
You're punishing yourself
because you're understanding

41:31.716 --> 41:36.118
that you didn't care about Donnie.

41:37.422 --> 41:40.256
Not really.

41:40.258 --> 41:42.692
That's what scares you.

41:42.694 --> 41:45.194
<i>♪♪♪</i>

41:45.196 --> 41:46.695
Yes.

41:46.697 --> 41:49.197
<i>♪♪♪</i>

41:49.199 --> 41:51.733
When I heard about Donnie's death, I...

41:51.735 --> 41:54.803
<i>♪♪♪</i>

41:54.805 --> 41:56.972
I felt relief.

41:56.974 --> 41:59.107
And all the rest... the
sorrow, the sadness...

41:59.109 --> 42:01.710
it was... it was buried way down.

42:01.712 --> 42:04.112
Like it didn't exist at all.

42:04.114 --> 42:05.580
That's right.

42:05.582 --> 42:07.715
<i>♪♪♪</i>

42:07.717 --> 42:11.686
So the question you've been
afraid to ask out loud,

42:11.688 --> 42:13.688
but have been whispering
to yourself ever since,

42:13.690 --> 42:16.324
do you wanna ask it?

42:16.326 --> 42:18.893
- Do I have to?
- I think you do.

42:18.895 --> 42:21.796
I can't say it for you.

42:21.798 --> 42:24.832
<i>♪♪♪</i>

42:27.704 --> 42:31.171
Well, people who have the
capacity to feel nothing...

42:31.173 --> 42:33.474
<i>♪♪♪</i>

42:33.476 --> 42:36.576
...they call them sociopaths.

42:36.578 --> 42:39.546
<i>♪♪♪</i>

42:39.548 --> 42:41.315
Is that what I am?

42:41.317 --> 42:42.883
<i>♪♪♪</i>

42:42.885 --> 42:44.851
What do you think?

42:44.853 --> 42:47.354
<i>♪♪♪</i>

42:47.356 --> 42:48.822
I don't know.

42:48.824 --> 42:51.025
<i>♪♪♪</i>

42:51.027 --> 42:54.327
<i>This</i> is how - you manifest guilt.

42:54.329 --> 42:55.428
If you didn't have it,

42:55.430 --> 42:57.130
you wouldn't have lost the money,

42:57.132 --> 42:58.932
you wouldn't be punishing yourself.

42:58.934 --> 43:03.737
But it is a... crucial time.

43:03.739 --> 43:08.474
Your switch plate is removed,
your wiring is exposed.

43:08.476 --> 43:11.444
Your blue ones go where your red
ones should, that's for sure.

43:11.446 --> 43:14.213
A normal person wouldn't
engage in the behavior.

43:14.215 --> 43:17.583
A sociopath wouldn't give a shit.

43:17.585 --> 43:19.552
You're somewhere in between.

43:19.554 --> 43:22.755
You are practiced at
turning off your feelings.

43:22.757 --> 43:25.024
Do it enough, it's a pattern.
Keep going, they die.

43:25.026 --> 43:28.126
So it's either fix it...

43:28.128 --> 43:30.629
<i>♪♪♪</i>

43:30.631 --> 43:34.199
...or close yourself back
up and see what happens.

43:34.201 --> 43:37.870
<i>♪♪♪</i>

43:37.872 --> 43:40.906
[helicopter blades whirring]

43:59.960 --> 44:04.195
[gate clattering]

44:04.197 --> 44:05.396
[switch clicks]

44:05.398 --> 44:06.564
Thank you, Anil.

44:06.566 --> 44:09.100
Really, thank you. I know this is weird.

44:09.102 --> 44:12.136
- [Lara chuckles]
- Anytime.

44:12.138 --> 44:14.271
Just keep it open till we're done.

44:14.273 --> 44:15.573
- Okay.
- Holy shit, Lar!

44:15.575 --> 44:18.142
Yeah, holy shit. [laughs]

44:18.144 --> 44:19.510
<i>[Ryan Adams] ♪ The light is harsh ♪</i>

44:19.512 --> 44:20.677
<i>♪ As it's breaking through the blinds ♪</i>

44:20.679 --> 44:21.812
- [sparkler hisses]
- [Kate gasps]

44:21.814 --> 44:24.115
<i>♪ Cross my face in black lines ♪</i>

44:24.117 --> 44:26.450
<i>♪ I'm so disconnected at
the foot of the bed ♪</i>

44:26.452 --> 44:28.986
- [fireworks popping, whistling]
<i>-♪ Don't know what to say,</i>

44:28.988 --> 44:30.387
<i>♪ Don't know what I said ♪</i>

44:30.389 --> 44:32.322
- Bright.
- So cool.

44:32.324 --> 44:34.557
<i>♪ Maybe every promise anybody makes ♪</i>

44:34.559 --> 44:36.459
- [laughing]
<i>- ♪ Is destined for the rocks ♪</i>

44:36.461 --> 44:38.028
<i>♪ The longer it takes ♪</i>

44:38.030 --> 44:41.665
<i>♪ Daylight is so close,
I can almost taste it ♪</i>

44:41.667 --> 44:44.901
<i>♪ It's all I got, it's not right ♪</i>

44:44.903 --> 44:47.137
<i>-♪ Everything is broken... ♪</i> -
[sirens wailing in distance]

44:47.139 --> 44:48.438
<i>♪ In my mind ♪</i>

44:48.440 --> 44:49.739
- Key part breaking the law?
- What?

44:49.741 --> 44:52.275
- Never mind. Come on.
- Ooh!

44:52.277 --> 44:54.043
- [siren wailing grows louder]
<i>-♪ Don't wanna lose control,</i>

44:54.045 --> 44:56.679
<i>♪ Baby, I just might ♪</i>

44:56.681 --> 45:00.150
<i>♪♪♪</i>

45:00.152 --> 45:01.984
[Wendy] What we did
tonight was pretty heavy.

45:01.986 --> 45:05.121
There might be aftershocks.

45:05.123 --> 45:07.356
Yeah, I know.

45:07.358 --> 45:10.693
You did to me what I do to companies.

45:10.695 --> 45:13.262
Took me apart, put me together again.

45:16.467 --> 45:19.702
You seem tired.

45:19.704 --> 45:21.770
Or are you just disgusted
at what you heard?

45:25.276 --> 45:29.578
Take this away with you.

45:29.580 --> 45:32.614
You <i> are</i> a difference maker,

45:32.616 --> 45:34.416
but you're not a god.

45:34.418 --> 45:35.884
<i>♪ pensive music ♪</i>

45:35.886 --> 45:38.319
Pancreatic takes everyone.

45:38.321 --> 45:40.055
It's like the market.
It does what it wants.

45:40.057 --> 45:44.659
And no magical thinking was
ever gonna change that.

45:44.661 --> 45:45.894
<i>♪♪♪</i>

45:45.896 --> 45:49.698
So no, I'm not disgusted with you.

45:49.700 --> 45:53.467
For whatever reason, when
it comes to you, that's...

45:53.469 --> 45:55.403
that's just not on the table.

45:55.405 --> 45:57.305
<i>♪♪♪</i>

45:57.307 --> 45:59.073
You know, some of <i> your</i> wires

45:59.075 --> 46:00.941
aren't where they should be, either.

46:00.943 --> 46:03.177
[chuckles]

46:03.179 --> 46:05.813
[inhales deeply]

46:05.815 --> 46:08.182
I can't argue.

46:08.184 --> 46:09.950
[inhales sharply]

46:09.952 --> 46:12.452
Is that why you've been
looking at other shops?

46:12.454 --> 46:16.456
<i>♪♪♪</i>

46:16.458 --> 46:18.859
That's what you've been
drilling for all night.

46:18.861 --> 46:22.029
Where were you thinking about?

46:22.031 --> 46:25.733
Was it Insight? Point One Four?

46:25.735 --> 46:27.434
<i>♪♪♪</i>

46:27.436 --> 46:28.968
No, Zenobia.

46:28.970 --> 46:30.970
[clicks teeth]

46:30.972 --> 46:32.672
<i>♪♪♪</i>

46:32.674 --> 46:35.542
Yeah, Zenobia.

46:35.544 --> 46:38.612
You think you'll be different there?

46:38.614 --> 46:41.047
Fixed?

46:41.049 --> 46:42.515
<i>♪♪♪</i>

46:42.517 --> 46:44.316
Working in a simpler, safer way

46:44.318 --> 46:47.120
will allow you to step
back from the edge?

46:47.122 --> 46:50.189
<i>♪♪♪</i>

46:50.191 --> 46:52.324
That's for a different session.

46:52.326 --> 46:53.993
[inhales sharply]

46:53.995 --> 46:57.029
<i>♪♪♪</i>

47:05.973 --> 47:08.374
Wait. Pull over here.

47:08.376 --> 47:10.643
Kill the lights.

47:10.645 --> 47:13.345
[gears shift, engine turns off]

47:13.347 --> 47:14.513
[door handle clicks]

47:15.849 --> 47:18.884
[crickets chirping]

47:36.202 --> 47:40.171
[indistinct conversation,
laughter in distance]

47:40.173 --> 47:43.207
<i>♪ tense music ♪</i>

47:50.983 --> 47:54.018
<i>♪♪♪</i>

48:02.028 --> 48:05.062
<i>[music intensifies]</i>

48:11.102 --> 48:13.903
[door handle clicks]

48:13.905 --> 48:16.072
[Chuck] Take me back to the city.

48:16.074 --> 48:19.108
<i>[The Black Heart Procession's
"Suicide" playing]</i>

48:21.380 --> 48:24.714
[door buzzes]

48:24.716 --> 48:26.182
[door closes]

48:26.184 --> 48:29.518
<i>♪♪♪</i>

48:29.520 --> 48:32.255
[door handle clicks]

48:32.257 --> 48:33.990
[man grunts loudly]

48:33.992 --> 48:35.225
<i>♪♪♪</i>

48:35.227 --> 48:36.525
[door closes]

48:36.527 --> 48:39.562
<i>♪♪♪</i>

48:48.272 --> 48:51.774
<i>♪ As my bones creak ♪</i>

48:51.776 --> 48:55.177
<i>♪ And my veins scream ♪</i>

48:55.179 --> 48:58.347
<i>♪ While my spirit breaks ♪</i>

48:58.349 --> 49:02.083
<i>♪ I hear you calling me ♪</i>

49:02.085 --> 49:05.653
<i>♪ As my heart aches ♪</i>

49:05.655 --> 49:09.056
<i>♪ And my hands shake ♪</i>

49:09.058 --> 49:11.426
- [knocks on door]
<i>-♪ While my mind fades ♪</i>

49:11.428 --> 49:14.662
- [Troy] Enter.
<i>- ♪ From these dark days ♪</i>

49:14.664 --> 49:15.930
[door handle clicks]

49:15.932 --> 49:18.565
<i>♪ In the valley where I come from ♪</i>

49:18.567 --> 49:20.200
<i>-♪ They'll cut your
wrists ♪</i> - [door closes]

49:20.202 --> 49:22.436
<i>♪ And hang you by the neck ♪</i>

49:22.438 --> 49:24.271
Mr. Martinez.

49:24.273 --> 49:25.472
<i>♪ I like your suicide ♪</i>

49:25.474 --> 49:28.842
It's been a long time.

49:28.844 --> 49:31.478
- Yes, it has.
<i>- ♪ I like your suicide ♪</i>

49:31.480 --> 49:34.014
[heels clacking]

49:34.016 --> 49:37.817
I can only assume

49:37.819 --> 49:40.186
you've been a wretched...

49:40.188 --> 49:41.388
- [inhales sharply]
- [jacket drops]

49:41.390 --> 49:43.623
[whispers] ...speck of shit.

49:43.625 --> 49:44.757
<i>♪♪♪</i>

49:44.759 --> 49:46.059
[clothing rustles]

49:46.061 --> 49:49.562
<i>-♪ As my heart aches ♪</i> - [clack]

49:49.564 --> 49:51.764
<i>♪ And my hands shake ♪</i>

49:51.766 --> 49:52.932
[exhales sharply]

49:52.934 --> 49:56.268
<i>♪ While my mind fades ♪</i>

49:56.270 --> 49:57.603
[whispers] Red.

49:57.605 --> 49:58.671
<i>- ♪ From these dark days ♪</i> - [grunts]

49:58.673 --> 50:00.339
- [thud]
- Red!

50:00.341 --> 50:02.442
- I'm sorry.
- [breathing heavily]

50:02.444 --> 50:04.444
Did I not pick up the body language?

50:04.446 --> 50:06.879
- It's been a while.
- No. Fuck!

50:06.881 --> 50:09.881
- [metal clacking]
- No.

50:09.883 --> 50:11.483
It's me. I can't.

50:11.485 --> 50:13.419
[metal clicking]

50:13.421 --> 50:15.454
I, uh...

50:15.456 --> 50:17.957
I didn't get permission.

50:20.828 --> 50:22.761
You didn't get permission from Mrs.
Martinez?

50:22.763 --> 50:24.229
[exhales sharply]

50:24.231 --> 50:26.097
Oh, my God. What are you doing here?

50:26.099 --> 50:28.834
[heels clacking, metal clanks]

50:28.836 --> 50:31.369
- I don't know.
- Go get permission.

50:31.371 --> 50:33.137
Yeah, it's not so simple.

50:33.139 --> 50:36.708
Does Wendy not role-play anymore?

50:36.710 --> 50:40.178
The workshop went so well.
She was a fucking all-star.

50:40.180 --> 50:41.812
It's like she's...

50:41.814 --> 50:44.082
[sighs]

50:44.084 --> 50:47.352
She's intractable.

50:47.354 --> 50:51.289
And she's so... [inhales sharply]

50:51.291 --> 50:52.957
So distant.

50:52.959 --> 50:55.360
Chuck...

50:55.362 --> 50:58.596
You guys should go see someone.

50:58.598 --> 51:00.397
You can both come here if you want.

51:00.399 --> 51:02.432
- [sighs]
- [muffled voices, banging]

51:02.434 --> 51:03.868
- [man] Who the fuck are you?
- [loud thud]

51:03.870 --> 51:05.469
[man] What the fuck you doing, man?

51:05.471 --> 51:07.337
- [Troy] What the fuck?
- [man grunts, groans]

51:09.441 --> 51:11.008
[bouncer] Asshole was taking pictures.

51:11.010 --> 51:14.244
Give me that. Give it to me!

51:14.246 --> 51:15.645
[camera clacks]

51:15.647 --> 51:18.681
<i>♪ tense music ♪</i>

51:21.186 --> 51:23.553
You've been following me all night?

51:23.555 --> 51:25.055
<i>♪♪♪</i>

51:25.057 --> 51:27.090
Oh, my God. I can't be here.

51:27.092 --> 51:28.658
I gotta go.

51:28.660 --> 51:31.694
<i>[music volume increases]</i>

51:33.031 --> 51:35.665
<i>[music intensifies]</i>

51:35.667 --> 51:36.833
[front door closes]

51:36.835 --> 51:39.869
[footsteps approach]

51:57.455 --> 51:58.887
[knife thuds]

52:02.260 --> 52:04.292
Must've been some party.

52:07.497 --> 52:09.698
We didn't go. We made our own.

52:09.700 --> 52:11.767
- [laughs]
- [sighs]

52:11.769 --> 52:13.301
How are you?

52:15.773 --> 52:18.306
I feel young again. Wanna go to prom?

52:18.308 --> 52:20.475
I know better than to
go with the bad boy.

52:20.477 --> 52:21.909
[singsongy] Do you?

52:21.911 --> 52:24.379
[singsongy] Maybe.

52:26.516 --> 52:29.717
I cry sometimes.

52:29.719 --> 52:31.852
At sentimental things.

52:31.854 --> 52:33.455
<i>♪ pensive music ♪</i>

52:33.457 --> 52:36.023
Commercials.

52:36.025 --> 52:37.792
And I don't tell you.

52:37.794 --> 52:41.596
<i>♪ sentimental music playing ♪</i>

52:41.598 --> 52:43.798
Okay.

52:43.800 --> 52:46.033
<i>♪♪♪</i>

52:46.035 --> 52:49.070
[inhales deeply, exhales slowly]

52:49.072 --> 52:51.906
I'm glad that tonight helped,

52:51.908 --> 52:55.409
but don't ever fucking
do that to me again.

52:55.411 --> 52:57.244
<i>♪♪♪</i>

52:57.246 --> 52:59.179
I don't think I will.

52:59.181 --> 53:02.149
<i>♪♪♪</i>

53:04.820 --> 53:05.885
[kiss]

53:23.238 --> 53:26.272
[typing on laptop]

53:31.012 --> 53:32.345
[key clicks]

53:39.120 --> 53:40.953
[glass clatters]

53:40.955 --> 53:42.221
[taps key]

53:43.791 --> 53:46.825
[typing]

53:51.365 --> 53:54.399
[continues typing]

53:58.539 --> 54:00.639
[laptop lid clicks]

54:02.176 --> 54:04.142
[exhales deeply]

54:05.345 --> 54:06.844
[door handle clicks]

54:06.846 --> 54:08.346
[door creaks]

54:10.750 --> 54:12.417
[door creaks]

54:12.419 --> 54:13.885
[door rattles shut]

54:13.887 --> 54:16.921
<i>♪ pensive music ♪</i>

54:19.458 --> 54:21.225
[keys jangle]

54:26.166 --> 54:29.433
[keys jangle]

54:29.435 --> 54:31.202
[exhales]

54:31.204 --> 54:34.205
[shower running]

54:34.207 --> 54:37.241
<i>♪♪♪</i>

54:41.347 --> 54:42.813
[exhales]

55:03.368 --> 55:04.567
[taps key]

55:04.569 --> 55:07.604
<i>♪♪♪</i>

55:14.246 --> 55:17.280
[typing]

55:23.687 --> 55:26.722
<i>[music volume increases]</i>

55:43.474 --> 55:45.840
[resumes typing]

55:45.842 --> 55:48.843
[keys clicking]

55:48.845 --> 55:51.846
[typing]

55:51.848 --> 55:55.516
<i>♪♪♪</i>

55:55.518 --> 55:56.785
[e-mail whooshes]

55:56.787 --> 55:59.821
<i>[Bob Dylan's "Gotta Serve
Somebody" playing]</i>

56:02.392 --> 56:03.524
[keys click]

56:03.526 --> 56:05.526
[faucet squeaks, shower stops running]

56:05.528 --> 56:07.662
[key clicks]

56:07.664 --> 56:11.032
<i>♪♪♪</i>

56:11.034 --> 56:15.903
<i>♪ You may be an ambassador
to England or France ♪</i>

56:15.905 --> 56:18.539
<i>♪ You may like to gamble ♪</i>

56:18.541 --> 56:21.475
<i>♪ You might like to dance ♪</i>

56:21.477 --> 56:22.876
- [bathroom door opens]
<i>-♪ You may be ♪</i>

56:22.878 --> 56:26.146
<i>♪ The heavyweight
champion of the world ♪</i>

56:26.148 --> 56:30.350
<i>♪ You might be a socialite
with a long string of pearls ♪</i>

56:30.352 --> 56:34.154
<i>♪ But you're gonna have
to serve somebody ♪</i>

56:34.156 --> 56:35.522
<i>♪ Yes, indeed ♪</i>

56:35.524 --> 56:38.292
<i>♪ You're gonna have to serve somebody ♪</i>

56:38.294 --> 56:41.361
<i>♪♪♪</i>

56:41.363 --> 56:45.431
<i>♪ Well, it may be the devil
or it may be the Lord ♪</i>

56:45.433 --> 56:49.168
<i>♪ But you're gonna have
to serve somebody ♪</i>

56:51.472 --> 56:54.173
<i>♪ You may be a rock 'n' roll addict ♪</i>

56:54.175 --> 56:56.508
<i>♪ Prancing' on the stage ♪</i>

